AWS Config Put Organization Conformance Pack:

$ aws --profile aws2 configservice put-organization-conformance-pack --organization-conformance-pack-name gendel-org-s3-bucket --delivery-s3-bucket awsconfigconforms-gendel --template-s3-uri s3://gendel-config-reports/aws-config-conformancepack-s3-bp.yaml
{
    "OrganizationConformancePackArn": "arn:aws:config:us-east-1:091042585556:organization-conformance-pack/gendel-org-s3-bucket-hvozvewk"
}


WHERE:

--organization-conformance-pack-name = My custom name for this conformance pack

--delivery-s3-bucket = The S3 bucket name which must begin with awsconfigconforms*

--template-s3-uri = the S3 URI that points to a valid template (you can also provide the template locally as a file)



AWS Config Put Organization Config Rule

$ aws --profile aws2 configservice put-organization-config-rule --organization-config-rule-name org-acm-certificate-expiration-check --organization-managed-rule-metadata '{"Description": "Org-ACM-Check","RuleIdentifier":"ACM_CERTIFICATE_EXPIRATION_CHECK","InputParameters":"{\"daysToExpiration\":\"14\"}", "ResourceTypesScope":["AWS::ACM::Certificate"]}'
{
    "OrganizationConfigRuleArn": "arn:aws:config:us-east-1:091042585556:organization-config-rule/org-acm-certificate-expiration-check-lbjiis3l"
}


WHERE:

--organization-config-rule-name = My custom name for this conformance pack

--organization-managed-rule-metadata = The required metadata to deploy a Config rule



